text.tspan: In-order to maintain continuity on board, following factors shall be taken into account pr planning reliefs:a) Following changes at the same time shall avoided: Master and Chief Engineer Master and Chief Officer Chief Engineer and Second Engineerb) Relief of more than 50% of the complement at one port shall be avoided unless the ship remains in the same port for a longerperiod.c) It is company policy to allow sufficient overlap for handing/ taking over at the time of crew change. This period of overlap shall beas follows:CategoryI – Overlap Period(Ex Staff and not on promotion)II – Overlap Period(New Staff or on promotion)Master1 – 2 days2 – 3 days which shall includean offshore operational trip(for Master on promotion refer to point e & f)Chief Engineer, Chief Officer and 2nd Engineer1 – 2 days2 – 3 daysDeck Officers and Engineers1 day1 – 2 daysOther Ranks1 day1 dayNote: For the purpose of above 1 day is to mean 8 working hours.d) Prior to arranging relief of any senior Officer (Master, C/O, C/E & 2/E) on board, Manning Office shall request that the off-signingsenior officer submits the handing over notes. A copy of handing over note is handed to concerned joining senior officer to study andthen discussed with the Superintendent as needed.e) When a Chief Officer is being promoted to the rank of Master, he should sail in parallel for 5 to 7 days with off signing Master whichshall include an offshore operational trip.f) If the officer completes one month of sailing in the junior rank before being elevated to the next rank, handover period as stipulatedin paragraph C, column II shall be considered sufficient.Note: Deviations to the above requires formal Risk Assessment to be carried out and approval from General Manager.4.19CREW APPRAISALS4.19.1APPRAISAL PROCESSa) Company has an extensive appraisal system for ship staff which includes safety and environmental awareness, ability and personaleffort and completion of these appraisal reports on PHOENIX is mandatory. The appraisal forms are designed to record informationpertinent to the performance as well as values-based characteristics of the individual and provide an opportunity for the individualsbeing appraised to note their comments.b) The objective is to identify the areas of strengths and weaknesses in an individual, and to assist him to grow and develop to be thebest he can whilst serving in our fleet.c) The appraisal system is an open type. Reports are to be discussed with the individual in a face-to-face meeting and individual givena chance to note his remarks. However the privilege accorded to the individual to respond to the reviewer, cannot be construed as aright to question the reviewer’s judgment.d) Proper adherence to the appraisal procedure contained herein can assist in cases where poor performance, attitude, orunacceptable behavior has been identified. These should be highlighted and recorded with examples during the appraisal meetingsand the individual given a chance to improve.e) The reports form an integral part in the officer’s career progression and cannot be left for the last minute. Appraisal meetingsrequire proper planning and it is strongly recommended that the reports completed well before the busy schedules of a port.4.19.2APPRAISAL MATRIXMasterC/EC/O2/EDeck StaffEngine StaffCateringStaffMasterXXXXXC/EXXC/OXXSupt’dAppraisalXX4.19.3APPRAISALS BY MASTER AND DEPT. HEADSRefer to Vessel Operations Manual Section 5.54.19.4SUPERINTENDENT APPRAISALSSuperintendents shall carry out an appraisal of the Master and Chief Engineer during shipboard visits for Audits and Inspections (VIR’s). An appraisal need not becarried out if it has been carried out within one month of the current visit.Superintendent appraisals are to be prepared using the PHOENIX Appraisal system. If this system is not operational, the appraisal can be made in hard copy usingthe appropriate form.On occasions, an evaluation may be sent by the superintendents/ managers to the crew department by email, if required by anycircumstance. These evaluations and feedback are also to be recorded in Phoenix.Superintendents can make appraisals of other staff if they wish to recognize good performance or highlight staff requiring attention.
